import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%b %d %Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 6))
    ax.plot(data['date'], data['price'], color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Date')
    ax.set_ylabel('Price')
    ax.set_title('What is the trend of S&P 500 index prices over time?')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['price'].plot(kind='hist', bins=50, color='blue', edgecolor='black', alpha=0.7)
    plt.axvline(data['price'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['price'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['price'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['price'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Price')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of S&P 500 index prices?')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%b %d %Y')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x='price', data=data, ax=ax, color='lightblue')
    ax.axvline(data['price'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Median: {data["price"].median():.2f}')
    ax.axvline(data['price'].quantile(0.25), color='green', linestyle='--', label=f'Q1: {data["price"].quantile(0.25):.2f}')
    ax.axvline(data['price'].quantile(0.75), color='green', linestyle='--', label=f'Q3: {data["price"].quantile(0.75):.2f}')
    ax.set_xlabel('Price')
    ax.set_ylabel('S&P 500 Index')
    ax.set_title('What is the average daily closing price of the S&P 500 index?')
    ax.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
from pandas.plotting import register_matplotlib_converters

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    register_matplotlib_converters()
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%b %d %Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 6))
    ax.plot(data['date'], data['price'], label='S&P 500 Index Price')
    ax.set_xlabel('Date')
    ax.set_ylabel('Price')
    ax.set_title('What is the volatility of S&P 500 index prices?')
    ax.legend(loc='upper left')
    ax.grid(True)
    ax.xaxis.set_tick_params(rotation=45)
    ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(plt.MaxNLocator(10))
    ax.xaxis.set_major_formatter(plt.DateFormatter('%Y-%m-%d'))
    ax.xaxis.set_minor_locator(plt.MaxNLocator(50))
    ax.xaxis.set_minor_formatter(plt.DateFormatter('%Y-%m-%d'))
    ax.fmt_xdata = plt.DateFormatter('%Y-%m-%d')
    ax.axhline(y=data['price'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Mean Price')
    ax.axhline(y=data['price'].max(), color='g', linestyle='--', label='Max Price')
    ax.axhline(y=data['price'].min(), color='b', linestyle='--', label='Min Price')
    ax.legend(loc='upper left')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
